Manchester City striker, Sergio Aguero, stands on his own as the highest goal scorer in the Premier League, after Match Day 6 fixtures. The Argentine scored once in their 8-0 humiliation of Watford on Sunday. Tammy Abraham and Teemu Pukki both failed to score, as their teams lost to Liverpool and Burnley respectively. Arsenal striker, Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang, however found the back of the net, as they came from behind to beat Aston Villa 3-2 at the Emirates. Premier League top scorers: 8 goals: Sergio Aguero (Manchester City) 7 goals: Tammy Abraham (Chelsea) 6 goals: Teemu Pukki (Norwich), Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang (Arsenal) 5 goals: Raheem Sterling (Manchester City) 4 goals: Mohamed Salah, Sadio Mane (Liverpool), Ashley Barnes (Burnley), Bernardo Silva (Manchester City), Callum Wilson (Bournemouth), Harry Kane (Tottenham) 3 goals: Roberto Firmino (Liverpool), Marcus Rashford (Manchester United), Jamie Vardy (Leicester), Sebastien Haller (West Ham), Daniel James (Manchester United), Mason Mount (Chelsea) Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.